File: Comair says flights on British Airways and Kulula could also be delayed. JOHANNESBURG - Airline operator Comair is warning of possible disruptions as some of its flights have been grounded.
The Civil Aviation Authority grounded the planes due to non-compliance. WATCH: Comair strike stopped It found irregularities at one of Comair's maintenance and technical service providers, SAA Technical. As a result., affected aircraft may not be flown until the necessary corrective action has been carried out. Comair says flights on British Airways and Kulula could also be delayed. WATCH: Numsa warns of severe impact of Comair strike It's advising customers to check the status of flights on their websites. It's not yet clear how many airlines are affected.